 As we come before Your throne to worship You.  By Your Spirit’s power You now draw our hearts,  And we hear Your voice in triumph ringing clear. 
(C) I am He that liveth, that liveth and was dead. 
 Behold I am alive for evermore. 
2 There we see You stand, mighty risen Lord, 
 Clothed in garments pure and holy, shining bright.  Eyes of flashing fire, feet like burnished bronze,  And the sound of many waters is Your voice. 
